[
    {
        "content": "<p>We have seen a proliferation of mod_whatever::foo::Flags being defined with essentially the same implementation for bitAnd, bitOr, contains and etc.</p>\n<p>We should have a single type, and anyone trying to reach for a <code>Flags</code> type can just wrap said type transparently:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">mod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">my_mod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"cp\">#[repr(transparent)]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Flags</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Flags</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MY_FLAGS_A</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Flags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Flags</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">bit</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">));</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"cm\">/* etc */</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I'm not really sure how we can make any ops transparently apply to the wrapper, as they will be defined for kernel::Flags here instead, but I think it should be doable.</p>\n<p>Thoughts?</p>",
        "id": 500362914,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1739873614
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You could use a macro to expose the ops.</p>",
        "id": 500364302,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1739874060
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In which case the common <code>Flags</code> type isn't actually necessary.</p>",
        "id": 500364369,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1739874080
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is a macro better than a trait?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">FlagsTrait</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Sized</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Flags</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">wrapper</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Flags</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"cm\">/* all other ops defined below, using inner() for the inner type</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">       and wrapper() to build the wrapper */</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">mod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">other_code</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Flags</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Flags</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">FlagTrait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Flags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Flags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">wrapper</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">flags</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Flags</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">flags</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 500367297,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1739874879
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess that's more verbose than a simple</p>\n<p><code>define_ops!(MyFlags)</code></p>",
        "id": 500367461,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1739874933
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>or<br>\n<code>define_flags!(MyFlags)</code></p>",
        "id": 500367503,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1739874950
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Your proposed <code>FlagsTrait</code> would not automatically give you ops such as <code>|</code></p>",
        "id": 500367679,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1739874990
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>well, you could have a blanket implementation right</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">FlagsTrait</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitOr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">bitor</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">wrapper</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">inner</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 500368292,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1739875200
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can't make a blanket impl for a trait you don't own.</p>",
        "id": 500371339,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1739876122
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would absolutely be willing to help with this, we have some flags in Kms as well that I would very much like some common infra for</p>",
        "id": 500530352,
        "sender_full_name": "Lyude",
        "timestamp": 1739921448
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The idea I had was a lot more simple: having a pattern like this for flags where we define two types for each new set of flags:<br>\n<code>SomeCoolFlags</code> ← a set of zero or more flags combined<br>\n<code>SomeCoolFlag</code> ← a single flag<br>\nThen defining a <code>macro_rules!()</code> macro for implementing all of the various bit arithematic traits on those two types. The reason I'd like to see this split into two types btw is so that <code>SomeCoolFlags</code> can still work fine with flags that might be defined on the C side but not on the rust side of things,</p>",
        "id": 500530774,
        "sender_full_name": "Lyude",
        "timestamp": 1739921675
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"690399\">@Lyude</span> </p>\n<p>For the actual implementation, I was thinking about letting <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"753286\">@Filipe Xavier</span> hack a bit on this. He's indicated that he wants to get more acquainted with the project and this task seems somewhat well-scoped for him. What do you think?</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The reason I'd like to see this split into two types btw is so that <code>SomeCoolFlags</code> can still work fine with flags that might be defined on the C side but not on the rust side of things,</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Can you give an example?</p>",
        "id": 500658305,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Almeida",
        "timestamp": 1739973862
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah I'd be happy to!</p>",
        "id": 500721437,
        "sender_full_name": "Lyude",
        "timestamp": 1739991531
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"753286\">@Filipe Xavier</span> so there's no macro here of course, but this is an example of one of the bitmasks that made me wonder about us having generic bitmask handling:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/// A bitmask for controlling the behavior of [`AtomicCommitTail::commit_planes`]</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// This corresponds to the `DRM_PLANE_COMMIT_*` flags on the C side. Note that this bitmask does</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// not discard unknown values in order to ensure that adding new flags on the C side of things does</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// not break anything in the future.</span>\n<span class=\"cp\">#[derive(Copy, Clone, Default, PartialEq, Eq)]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">From</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlag</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">from</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PlaneCommitFlag</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">From</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">from</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitOr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">bitor</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitOrAssign</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">bitor_assign</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitAnd</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">bitand</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitAndAssign</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">bitand_assign</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitOr</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlag</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">bitor</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PlaneCommitFlag</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitOrAssign</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlag</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">bitor_assign</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PlaneCommitFlag</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitAnd</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlag</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">bitand</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PlaneCommitFlag</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">from</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">BitAndAssign</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlag</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">bitand_assign</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"k\">mut</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PlaneCommitFlag</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rhs</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">PlaneCommitFlags</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Create a new bitmask</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">new</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">default</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"sd\">/// Check if the bitmask has the given commit flag set</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">has</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">flag</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">PlaneCommitFlag</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">bool</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&amp;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">flag</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">==</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">flag</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">into</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Where <code>PlaneCommitFlag</code> is an enum for a single flag, and <code>PlaneCommitFlags</code> is a bitmask of zero or more flags combined. IMO I like this solution since it gives us a nice enum to work with, shouldn't break if new bitmask values are added to the C side and not the rust side, etc.</p>",
